	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah that's pretty much what I meant by it being easier to set up the first time.  Instead of using a screw driver to remove socketed chips, use 2 stacked sockets - it gets a good connection but can pop out with less force than a CF card.
<br />
<br />For a front-loader, you can put the cart in first, then put the ROMs in afterwards, and not have to remove the cart from the NES.  But a toploader is easier all around, with a bare PCB.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
